        "filename": "page_001.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 2,
      "content": "One day, Nutkin's family sailed across the lake. They went to Owl Island in their boat.",
      "source_page_number": 2,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_002.jpg",
        "filename": "page_002.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_002.mp3",
        "filename": "page_002.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 3,
      "content": "They gave Old Brown Owl three mice as a gift. They asked if they could gather nuts there.",
      "source_page_number": 3,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_003.jpg",
        "filename": "page_003.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_003.mp3",
        "filename": "page_003.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 4,
      "content": "Old Brown Owl took the gift. He let them gather many fun nuts.",
      "source_page_number": 4,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_004.jpg",
        "filename": "page_004.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_004.mp3",
        "filename": "page_004.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 5,
      "content": "All the squirrels worked hard. Only Nutkin stopped to play.",
      "source_page_number": 5,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_005.jpg",
        "filename": "page_005.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_005.mp3",
        "filename": "page_005.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 6,
      "content": "Nutkin danced and told Old Brown riddles. The owl looked very puzzled.",
      "source_page_number": 6,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_006.jpg",
        "filename": "page_006.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_006.mp3",
        "filename": "page_006.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 7,
      "content": "Day after day they brought gifts. But Nutkin teased the old owl more.",
      "source_page_number": 7,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_007.jpg",
        "filename": "page_007.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_007.mp3",
        "filename": "page_007.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 8,
      "content": "Old Brown Owl warned Nutkin. He said, \"Stop teasing me!\"",
      "source_page_number": 8,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_008.jpg",
        "filename": "page_008.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_008.mp3",
        "filename": "page_008.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 9,
      "content": "But Nutkin did not listen to Old Brown. Suddenly whoosh! Old Brown caught him in his strong claws.",
      "source_page_number": 9,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_009.jpg",
        "filename": "page_009.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_009.mp3",
        "filename": "page_009.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 10,
      "content": "Nutkin wiggled and tried to get away. But he left most of his tail in the owl's claws!",
      "source_page_number": 10,
      "image": {
        "path": "images/page_010.jpg",
        "filename": "page_010.jpg",
        "content_type": "image/jpeg"
      },
      "audio": {
        "path": "voices/book_level_2/page_010.mp3",
        "filename": "page_010.mp3",
        "content_type": "audio/mpeg",
        "provider": "kokoro",
        "language": "en",
        "model": "hexgrad/Kokoro-82M"
      }
    },
    {
      "page_number": 11,
      "content": "Nutkin went home very quiet that day. He learned being polite is always the best way.",
      "source_page_number": 11,
      "image": {
